description: {"blocks":[{"key":"f2c6d","text":"West Nile virus (WNV), a  member of the family Flaviviridae, genus Flavivirus is a mosquito-borne emerging pathogen, which is endemic in most part of Europe, especially in the central and southern regions of the continent. The vast majority of human infections remains asymptomatic, though approximately 20% of infected individuals develops milder, influenza-like disease and less than 1% has severe neurological manifestation. Besides the application of  serological and molecular diagnostic techniques, virus isolation and molecular typing of virus isolates are the most important reference laboratory activities. Here we summarize a brief description of our protocol for WNV isolation on cell cultures.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":47,"length":12},{"style":"italic","offset":67,"length":11}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.section: WNV isolation from PCR positive clinical samples:
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"3k23a","text":"Cell lines: Vero or Vero E6, that are suitable for West Nile virus. Cell culture should be grown in T25 or T75 cell culture flasks.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":27}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"attgb","text":"- Cell culture medium: DMEM (Dulbecco's Modified Eagle Medium) high (4,5 g/L) glucose with L-Glutamine 1000L (Lonza; Catalog #: BE15-604K; ).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":2,"length":25}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"81kd7","text":"- 5% Foetal Bovine Serum (FBS) (Merck; Catalog F7524)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":2,"length":28}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":47,"length":5}],"data":{}},{"key":"ftj3i","text":"- Antibiotic: Cell Culture Guard, in a dilution 1:100 (ITW Reagents; Catalog A8906,0050)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":2,"length":30}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"48tdg","text":"- Incubator: 37°C, 5% CO2 concentration.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":24,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"47on9","text":"Note: Prior to the virus isolation, cells should be seeded. After 24-48 hours later, when the cell monolayers are  at 80-90% confluence, cell cultures can be used for virus inoculation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"61C4735FA17511ED93D40A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://www.sigmaaldrich.com/HU/en/product/sigma/f7524"}}}}

steps.section: WNV isolation from PCR positive clinical samples:
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"578fo","text":"Samples: PCR positive clinical specimens:  serum, plasma or urine.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1at28","text":"Note: Urine samples must be filtered on 0.22 µm pore size membrane filters and treated with 0.01 M TRIS buffer to adjust the  pH to 7.2 to 7.8 prior inoculation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6jseh","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: WNV isolation from PCR positive clinical samples:
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"jhsd","text":"Add 1 - 2 ml sample to a T75 cell culture flask or 0.5 ml sample to a T25 flask. Incubate at 37°C in 5% CO2 concentration for 90 minutes. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":106,"length":2},{"style":"bold","offset":126,"length":12}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6e2nb","text":"Note: if the sample volume is insuffiecient, complete the volume with cell culture medium.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: WNV isolation from PCR positive clinical samples:
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"34vct","text":"After the incubation, do not remove the virus inoculum. Add cell culture medium (DMEM) with 5% FBS and cell culture guard in a dilution 1:100.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":22,"length":32}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: WNV isolation from PCR positive clinical samples:
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"6n88e","text":"Incubate at 37°C in 5% CO2 concentration for up to 7 days. Daily monitoring of the presence of any cytophatic effects is recommended. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":57},{"style":"sub","offset":25,"length":2}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: WNV isolation from PCR positive clinical samples:
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"at3e7","text":"At day 7 cells should be harvested. A blind passage is recommended, using both the cell culture supernatant and harvested cells. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":8}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
